Australian government report suggests carbon dioxide produced by burning fossil fuels could be captured and used to produce the fizz in Cola . 
  Many nations are looking into Carbon Capture and Storage (CCS) technologies as a way to cut their greenhouse house emissions . 
  CCS refers to the process of capturing carbon released by burning Fossil fuels and storing it in porous rock layers . 
  But the report says there is no commercial CO2 re-use in Australia . 
 